OL,6,F"In essence, this is a laissez faire
OL,7,Feconomy. Schools can decide what they
OL,8,Fwant to teach
OL,10,FSo at the black curriculum, we're
OL,11,Fhoping for black history to be
OL,12,Fembedded in the national curriculum.
OL,14,FI'm understanding more and more that
OL,15,Fmore schools are actually not using
OL,16,Fthe national curriculum. So it might
OL,17,Fbe more beneficial for teachers to be
OL,18,Ftrained to learn black history and to
OL,19,Fteach it confidently from, you know,
