OL,6,FThere are also criticisms that when
OL,7,FBlack History is opted to be taught in
OL,8,Fschools, it is only through the narrow
OL,9,Fperspective of triumph over adversity.
OL,10,FInforming students of Britain's role
OL,11,Fin the transatlantic slave trade,
OL,12,Ffollowed by outlawing it. Or the civil
OL,13,Frights movement in the United States.
OL,15,FThe overall impact of colonialism and
OL,16,Fthe British Empire is often overlooked
OL,17,Fand restricted to within higher
OL,18,Feducation settings.
