OL,3,COctober is Black History Month, but is
OL,4,Cit time schools taught it all year?
OL,6,F"We don't have enough black history on
OL,7,Fthe curriculum, and the things that we
OL,8,Fdo learn in black history are limited
OL,9,Fto slavery and maybe some American
OL,10,Fblack history, which is not reflective
OL,11,Fof the society that we have here.
OL,13,FWhat we're really trying to do is
OL,14,Fbuild wider narratives. looking at
OL,15,Fpeople who traveled from other parts
OL,16,Fof the world before colonisation to
OL,17,Fthe parts of history that are more
OL,18,Fcontemporary and current, like
OL,19,FGrenfell, that are part of our story,
OL,20,Four national story, because again,
OL,21,Fthere's history within that."
